-- U.S. Justice Dept official says expects more mortgage case activity soon
-- By Aruna Viswanatha
-- Mon Jul 14, 2014 10:32AM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, July 14 (Reuters) - U.S. Associate Attorney General Tony West said on Monday that the American public can expect to hear more from the Justice Department's residential mortgage-backed securities working group in the "very near future."

